    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECTATORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Spectators are individuals present at the rally race, showing interest and support for the event while witnessing the thrilling activity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spectators are individuals who attend racing events to watch and support their favorite teams and drivers, contributing to the lively atmosphere of the event."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spectators are individuals who attend rally racing events, engaging with the competition and supporting the drivers through cheers and capturing moments with cameras."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spectators refer to the fans who gather to watch and cheer during the rally event, highlighting the excitement and public interest in the sport."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spectators are the audience present at the go-kart racing event, observing the race and contributing to the atmosphere of excitement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The spectators are the enthusiastic crowd present at the FIA World Endurance Championship event, celebrating and showing excitement for the racing achievements."</data>
