    <node id="&quot;TROPHY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A trophy represents an award given to winners or outstanding participants in racing events, symbolizing achievement and recognition in sports."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is a physical award presented to individuals during the FIA Awards, symbolizing achievement and excellence in the motorsports field."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is a prestigious award presented at the FIA World Rallycross Championship’s award ceremony, symbolizing achievement in the sport."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is a prestigious award presented during the ceremony, symbolizing success and recognition within the rally racing community."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is a star-shaped award that symbolizes achievement in the racing event, held by champions during the ceremony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is a symbol of victory, intricately designed and held by individuals during the award ceremony, signifying their accomplishments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is an award presented at the FIA Awards 2019, recognizing outstanding achievements in the FIA Formula 2 Championship and was specifically awarded to Isaac Hajar and Invictor Racing."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is an award presented during the ceremony to recognize outstanding achievements by participants in the motorsport event."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy is an award symbolizing achievement in racing, often presented during celebrations at motorsport events, indicating success and recognition."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy represents an award given to individuals for their achievements, prominently displayed during the FIA Awards 2023."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy represents the award given to outstanding performers like Max Verstappen at the FIA Awards 2024, symbolizing their achievements in racing."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy represents the physical recognition awarded to winners in the FIA World Endurance Hypercar Championship, symbolizing excellence in motorsport."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy symbolizes achievement and success, prominently displayed during the awards ceremony as a recognition of the participants' accomplishments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy symbolizes recognition and achievement, specifically awarded to Kenzel Craigie during the FIA Awards ceremony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Trophy symbolizes victory in racing and is awarded to the winners of Formula One events, representing the achievements of drivers like Charles Leclerc."&lt;SEP&gt;"Trophy represents the award given to winners and top performers in Formula One races, symbolizing their success and excellence in the sport."</data>
