    <node id="&quot;AWARD CEREMONY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An Award Ceremony is a formal event to recognize and celebrate the achievements of individuals or teams in various domains, such as sports, often involving the presentation of trophies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Award Ceremony is a formal event recognizing the achievements within the motorsport community, celebrating significant contributions and victories."&lt;SEP&gt;"Award Ceremony signifies recognition for exceptional achievements in motorsport, often involving trophies and honors for outstanding performance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a celebratory event where individuals receive trophies for recognition and achievement, reflecting a festive atmosphere and camaraderie among participants."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event celebrating achievements in rally racing, where teams and individuals receive awards for their accomplishments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event celebrating the achievements of drivers in the ABB Formula E Championship, featuring presentations and recognitions for outstanding performances."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event characterized by vibrant lighting and the recognition of champions in racing, including Giuseppe Palomba and Ethan Jeff Hall."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event designed to recognize and honor significant achievements within the world of motorsports."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event recognizing the achievements in Formula 1, characterized by an elegant atmosphere and attendee engagement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony is a formal event recognizing the achievements of drivers in the FIA World Rallycross Championship, characterized by the presentation of trophies."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony represents the event where achievements in the FIA racing categories are celebrated, including various awards and recognitions for teams and drivers."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Award Ceremony serves as the formal event where awards are presented to recipients, highlighting accomplishments and excellence."</data>
