      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A podium is a platform where award presentations occur, serving as a central focus during racing award ceremonies."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is a central feature of the FIA Awards 2024 where award recipients, like Max Verstappen, receive their honors during the ceremony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is a significant feature of the FIA Awards 2023, associated with the presentation of trophies to award recipients."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is a significant structure in the Award Ceremony where winners are acknowledged and awards are presented."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is a structure used during official events like the awards ceremony where awards are presented to recipients."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is the elevated platform used during the award ceremony for presenters and award recipients, symbolizing honor and recognition in the event."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium is the platform where drivers celebrate their victories, showcasing the top finishers in a Formula One race."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium serves as the elevated platform where the presenters and award recipients stand during the awards ceremony, highlighting the significance of the event."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium serves as the focal point for presentations and speeches during the awards ceremony, marked by the FIA Awards logo."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium serves as the focal point for speeches and presentations during the awards ceremony, adorned with significant logos and branding."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Podium showcases the speakers and presenters during the FIA Awards ceremony, serving as a central point for announcements and speeches."&lt;SEP&gt;"The podium at the AWARDS KIGAU 2024 serves as the focal point for presentations and speeches, highlighting the significance of the event."&lt;SEP&gt;"The podium is a central feature of the awards ceremony, where presenters stand to address the audience and deliver important messages."</data>
