    <node id="&quot;AWARDS CEREMONY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "Awards Ceremony" is a prestigious formal event that serves to recognize and celebrate outstanding achievements in the realm of motorsports. It is a significant occasion within the FIA Awards framework, reflecting excellence not only in motorsport but also across various fields associated with the FIA, including events like the FIFA Awards 2023 and the FIA Awards Kigali 2024. This celebration showcases the accomplishments of champions across multiple categories, including the FIA World Endurance Championship, the Dakar Rally, and the FIA World Rally-Raid Championship.

The Awards Ceremony is characterized by a celebratory atmosphere, where award presentations, speeches, and interviews highlight the individual performances of both drivers and teams. Participants can expect a decorated setting with an audience, often adorned in formal attire, creating an engaging and emotional environment. The ceremony embodies the growth and significance of the FIA over its 120 years, emphasizing community recognition within motorsports.

Various award categories are featured, including the revered Lifetime Achievement Award, as the ceremony honors not only competitive racing achievements but also contributions made by individuals and organizations in the motorsport sector. The event includes trophy presentations, showcasing nominees and celebrating winners, thus culminating in an event revered for its recognition of excellence in racing and motorsports as a whole. Overall, the Awards Ceremony represents a formal gathering where success in motorsports is both acknowledged and celebrated in an elegant setting.</data>
